title Invoice Creation, Management & Sending Workflow

actor User
participant Browser
participant "Web App\n(React SPA)" as Web
participant "API\n(Node.js)" as API
participant "Database\n(PostgreSQL)" as DB
participant "PDF Service\n(pdfkit)" as PDF
participant "Email Service\n(nodemailer / Gmail)" as Email
participant "Client\n(Invoice Recipient)" as Client

note over User,Client: ── Create Invoice ───────────────────────────────────

User->Browser: Navigate to Invoices → "Create Invoice"
Web->API: GET /v1/clients?active=true
API->DB: SELECT * FROM clients WHERE isActive=true
DB-->API: Client list
API-->Web: Clients
Web-->User: Client dropdown

User->Browser: Select client "Acme Corp"
Web->API: GET /v1/time-entries?clientId=<acmeId>&isBilled=false
API->DB: SELECT te.*, p.name, p.costPerHour, c.name\nFROM time_entries te\nJOIN projects p ON te.projectId=p.id\nJOIN clients c ON p.clientId=c.id\nWHERE c.id=? AND te.isBilled=false AND te.userId=?\nORDER BY te.date

DB-->API: Unbilled time entries for Acme
API-->Web: { data: timeEntries }
Web-->User: Grouped list of unbilled entries with hours + amounts

User->Browser: Select entries (May + June 2026)\nSet: issueDate, dueDate, taxRate=8%, notes="Net 30"
Browser->Web: Click "Create Invoice"
Web->Web: Validate form (Zod)
Web->API: POST /v1/invoices\n{ clientId, issueDate, dueDate, periodStart, periodEnd,\n  timeEntryIds: [...], taxRate: 8, notes: "Net 30" }

API->API: Validate request (Zod)
API->API: Verify JWT, extract userId
API->DB: SELECT * FROM time_entries WHERE id IN (...) AND isBilled=false
DB-->API: Verify all entries exist and are unbilled
API->DB: SELECT invoicePrefix FROM users WHERE id=?
DB-->API: User's prefix (e.g., "ACME")
API->DB: SELECT MAX(invoiceNumber) FROM invoices\nWHERE invoiceNumber LIKE 'ACME-2026-%'
DB-->API: Last sequence number
API->API: Generate number: "ACME-2026-0042"
API->API: Calculate line item amounts: hours × costPerHour\nSubtotal = sum(amounts)\nTaxAmount = subtotal × taxRate / 100\nTotal = subtotal + taxAmount

API->DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION\nINSERT INTO invoices { status: DRAFT, invoiceNumber, ... }\nINSERT INTO invoice_items [...]\nUPDATE time_entries SET isBilled=true WHERE id IN (...)\nCOMMIT

DB-->API: Invoice + items created
API-->Web: 201 { data: { invoice, items } }
Web-->User: Invoice detail page (status: DRAFT)\nLine items, subtotal, tax, total

note over User,Client: ── Review and Open ──────────────────────────────────

User->Browser: Review invoice, click "Mark as Open"
Web->API: PATCH /v1/invoices/:id/status { status: "OPEN" }
API->API: Validate status transition DRAFT → OPEN
API->DB: UPDATE invoices SET status='OPEN' WHERE id=?
DB-->API: Updated
API-->Web: 200 { data: updatedInvoice }
Web-->User: Status badge: OPEN

note over User,Client: ── Generate & Preview PDF ───────────────────────────

User->Browser: Click "Preview PDF"
Web->Browser: GET https://api.timekeeping.local/v1/invoices/:id/pdf\n(opens in new tab)
Browser->API: GET /v1/invoices/:id/pdf\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>
API->DB: SELECT invoice + items + client + user\nFROM invoices JOIN ...
DB-->API: Full invoice data

API->PDF: buildInvoicePdf(invoiceData)
note over PDF: pdfkit renders:\n- Company header\n- Bill To: client info\n- Invoice # / Date / Due Date\n- Line items table\n- Subtotal / Tax / Total\n- Notes / Payment terms

PDF-->API: PDF Buffer
API-->Browser: 200 Content-Type: application/pdf\nContent-Disposition: inline; filename="ACME-2026-0042.pdf"
Browser-->User: PDF rendered in new tab

note over User,Client: ── Send Invoice ─────────────────────────────────────

User->Browser: Click "Send Invoice"
Web-->User: Confirm dialog:\n"Send to client@acmecorp.com?"
User->Browser: Confirm Send

Web->API: POST /v1/invoices/:id/send
API->API: Validate status is OPEN or RESENT
API->DB: SELECT invoice + items + client + user
DB-->API: Full invoice data

API->PDF: buildInvoicePdf(invoiceData)
PDF-->API: PDF Buffer

API->Email: sendInvoiceEmail({\n  to: client.email,\n  subject: "Invoice ACME-2026-0042 from TimeKeeping",\n  htmlBody: renderInvoiceEmailTemplate(invoice),\n  attachment: pdfBuffer\n})

Email->Client: 📧 Email + PDF attachment
note over Email,Client: Gmail SMTP via App Password

Client-->Email: (delivery receipt)
Email-->API: Sent successfully

API->DB: UPDATE invoices SET status='SENT', sentAt=NOW()
DB-->API: Updated
API-->Web: 200 { data: { status: 'SENT', sentAt: '...' } }
Web-->User: Toast: "Invoice sent to client@acmecorp.com"\nStatus badge: SENT

note over User,Client: ── Resend Invoice ───────────────────────────────────

User->Browser: Click "Resend"
Web->API: POST /v1/invoices/:id/send (same endpoint)
note over API: status SENT → RESENT on resend
API->PDF: Re-generate PDF
PDF-->API: PDF Buffer
API->Email: Resend with "Reminder:" subject prefix
Email->Client: 📧 Reminder email
API->DB: UPDATE SET status='RESENT', resentAt=NOW()
DB-->API: Updated
API-->Web: 200 status: RESENT

note over User,Client: ── Track Payment ────────────────────────────────────

Client-->User: Client pays invoice

User->Browser: Click "Mark as Paid"
Web->API: PATCH /v1/invoices/:id/status { status: "PAID" }
API->API: Validate: SENT|RESENT → PAID
API->DB: UPDATE SET status='PAID', paidAt=NOW()
DB-->API: Updated
API-->Web: Status: PAID + paidAt date shown

User->Browser: Click "Close Invoice"
Web->API: PATCH /v1/invoices/:id/status { status: "PAID_CLOSED" }
API->API: Validate: PAID → PAID_CLOSED
API->DB: UPDATE SET status='PAID_CLOSED', closedAt=NOW()
DB-->API: Updated
API-->Web: Status: PAID_CLOSED (archived)

note over User,Client: ── Download Invoice PDF ─────────────────────────────

User->Browser: Click "Download PDF"
Web->Browser: GET /v1/invoices/:id/pdf?download=true
API->PDF: buildInvoicePdf(invoiceData)
PDF-->API: PDF Buffer
API-->Browser: 200 Content-Disposition: attachment;\nfilename="ACME-2026-0042.pdf"
Browser-->User: PDF downloaded
